According to the analyses, the comet is on a so-called hyperboola orway, which leads it out of our system - and clearly of interstellar origin, as the International Astronomical Union (IAU) indicated. It is also responsible for the naming and categorization of celestial bodies. In honor of its discoverer, the interstellar tail star, which was initially listed under the catalogue number C / 2019 Q4, was given the designation 2I / Borisov, whereby the first part of the name indicates that it is the second interstellable object that was discovered in our solar system.
